etymology.description: Depicts a carving or engraving -> Proto-form of 㓞(㓞) (jiè, 'aid') -> Unrelated to 丰(豐) (fēng, 'abundance')
etymology.interpretation: The character 丯(丯) (jiè, 'aid') is a pictogram representing something carved or engraved. It is an early form of the character 㓞(㓞) (jiè, 'aid'), unrelated to other characters like 丰(豐) (fēng, 'abundance') and 王(王) (wáng, 'king').
